com.samysadi.acs.service.migration

Interface MigrationHandler

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Cloneable, Entity, Notifier, Probed
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MigrationHandlerDefault

    public interface MigrationHandler
extends Entity
    A migration handler defines methods for handling migration of a virtual machine from one host to another.

    Depending on the implementations you should check the value returned by the supportsLiveMigration() method to see if the migration process is live or cold.
    Likewise you should check the value returned by the supportsStorageMigration() to see if the storage is also copied during the migration or not.

    Note you cannot migrate a virtual machine that is already being migrated, if you try to do so an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Samy Sadi , Belabbas Yagoubi

        Creates a clone of this entity and sets its parent to null.

        This is a deep clone method which also clones children entities and sets their parents to the newly created clone.

        Implementations must ensure that the new clone will be independent from the current entity.

      • supportsStorageMigration

        boolean supportsStorageMigration()
        Returns true if the storage is also copied during the migration. This method returns false if the storage is not copied during the migration process, so that the migrated VM will continue to use its old storage.

        You probably want to use a migration handler that does not support storage migration if the storage is a SAN storage that is accessible from the new host.

        Returns:
        true if the storage is also copied during the migration

      • migrate

        void migrate(VirtualMachine vm,
           Host destinationHost)
        Migrates the given virtual machine vm to the destination host.
        The virtual machine may remain running for some time when it is being transmitted to destination host.

        A NotificationCodes.MIGRATION_SUCCESS notification is thrown if the virtual machine was successfully migrated.
        A NotificationCodes.MIGRATION_ERROR notification is thrown if an error happens when the virtual machine is being migrated.

        Additionally, the given vm is notified using a NotificationCodes.VM_MIGRATED notification to let it know that it was migrated.

        Parameters:
        vm - the VirtualMachine that will be migrated
        destinationHost - the Host that will receive the new vm
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the given vm is already being migrated (see VirtualMachine.FLAG_IS_MIGRATING).
